N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 17 ยง 922.3 - Tensile strength of material

State Regulations

When the tensile strength of steel or wrought iron shell
plates is not known, it shall be taken at 50,000 pounds for steel and 45,000
pounds for wrought iron. Notes
